<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[158,801,546,697]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[158,274,546,569]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from all other cynolebiatins by having flank red with bright blue bars on the anterior portion and vertical rows of blue dots on the posterior portion in males (a condition modified in 
<taxonomicName box="[394,547,641,665]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cholopteryx">
<emphasis box="[394,547,641,665]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">S. cholopteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in which there are blue bars on the entire flank).
</paragraph>
